description: Before Cassie and Vlad ever smashed a head, another duo patrolled the night: the fearsome NIGHTMARE and his sidekick SLEEPY! What is their bizarre connection to Samhain, and how will this all lead into a teen sidekick / slasher movie mash-up?
name: Super Sidekick Sleepover Slaughter, prelude

description: A story of Chapel's past years before Youngblood.

What do a Golden Age hero, a Western hero and a romance heroine have in common? They all join the Avengers during one of the team's busier eras, presented here! Worlds, centuries and genres clash as the Avengers battle Kang in the past and the Serpent Crown on the Earth next door! Then, when civil war grips both Atlantis and Latveria, which side must the Avengers take? If it's up to Doctor Doom, it'll be the evil they know, not the evil they don't! Plus: Graviton, the Grim Reaper, voodoo, mad science and more! Featuring the Champions, the Squadron Supreme and the Circus of Crime!

Reprints Avengers (1963) #141-163, Annual #6, and Super-Villain Team-Up #9.
name: Volume 7

description: Rowan and Shing, exhausted after their vicious battle with each other in issue #2, are now confronted with the assembled might of the Children of the Damned! Meanwhile, the U.S. government dispatches a special agent to defuse the potential political fallout from the theft of the Arkanium scrolls. This agent, Commander Marissa Wheeler, has a deep and sinister connection to one of our heroes that may destroy his life. As the battle reaches a fever pitch, and Rowan and Shing stand on the verge of defeat, a sacrifice is made, a sacred place is lost, and the destructive power of the scrolls is made painfully obvious. Issue #3 is an action packed battle-fest that features the amazing abilities of the Children of the Damned for the first time!
name: None

description: Rowan and Shing, demoralized and shell-shocked after the devastating attack from Moukie and his Children of the Damned, realize that they have no time to regroup because a United Nations special-forces unit is hot on their trail. Shing's life-long friend and confidant, Sasha, is now a captive of the Children. Yet she uses her hostage situation as a way of learning more about the dark designs of Moukie and his mad lust for the power of the Arkanium scrolls. Sash uncovers the puzzle of the bizarre connection that links the destinies of Rowan, Shing, and Moukie while one member of the Children of the Damned makes his play for dominance. As Act One of Arkanium comes to a senses-shattering conclusion, secrets are revealed, ghosts from the past are resurrected, and the bounds of heroism are pushed to their ultimate limits. This is the crucial issue that propels our heroes onto the road of their uncertain fate.
name: None

description: Rowan, reeling from the constant defeats and the revelation that Marissa is alive, decides to go on the offensive. Shing warns him that the threat they face is much more insidious than previously believed. Meanwhile, Moukie taunts the kidnapped Sasha with his plans of global domination and how the scrolls affect mankind's evolutionary potential. Kyle secretly has other designs for the scrolls, and Sirena, manipulated by Moukie, pushes Kyle to see how far he will go. Issue #5 is the beginning of Act Two of the "Arkanium Saga" and it is a perfect jumping-on point for new readers. With each passing moment, the stakes are raised and mankind is pushed closer to the brink of oblivion.
name: None

description: In a war without limits, against an enemy without number, a radically new breed of soldier is the only possible response. As the Dark Matter forces of the Progeny sweep through the universe, deconstructing the very stuff of space itself, five recruits step into the firing line, wrapped in living battle-suits. Unknown to them, though, they've been selected not to do... but rather to die! All-new, sweeping Sci-Fi action from Simon Furman (Transformers: The War Within) and hot new talent Adi Granov!

Caught up in the machinations of friend and foe alike, Damien Arnaz and Ebon Squad descend further into the sucking maelstrom of their new, altered existence. Unsure who to trust, flailing angrily at fate, they take up arms, but on their own terms.

Thought you'd heard the last of Fred 'Ferret' McGlone, Harry Hornby and Digby Bolton? They were the Trident newspaper's finest war reporters in a bygone era. But Ferret still has a few tall tales to tell - and they're all true, of course...Like the time the intrepid newsmen went to cover the war in the Sudan, and Digby had swapped his sketch pad and pencils for a new-fangled cine camera.Get ready to read their desert despatches.

By: Norman Adams

description: The manhunt is on! As director of S.H.I.E.L.D., Tony Stark had sole possession of a database that contained the secret identities of every registered hero in the country. But now, S.H.I.E.L.D. is no more. A casuality in the aftermath of the Skrull's Secret Invasion, the international peacemaking organization has been replaced by the Dark Reign of Norman Osborn and his newly convieved H.A.M.M.E.R. - a less kind, a less gentle remaking of the legendary security force founded by Nick fury. Osborn now has all the power he ever wanted minus the most important ingrediant, the registation database, which is stored in the only place Stark could guarantee it's safe keeping - inside his Extremis-enhanced brain. With Tony Stark in disgrace and on the run, the orders have come down from the highest level to every mercenary, mobster and osborn minion: "Bring me the head of Tony Stark!' Collecting INVINCIBLE IRON MAN #8-13.
name: World's Most Wanted, Part 1

volume.name: Invincible Iron Man: World's Most Wanted, Part One

description: Don't miss out on this critically acclaimed blockbuster! Tony's failing health makes the Iron Man too complicated to pilot. Hill hunts the world's most un-huntable man. Pepper defies Norman osborn and H.A.M.M.E.R. itself. And all of Iron Man's rogues' gallery is after him and the billion-dollar bounty on his head...starting with the murderous Madame Masque! But believe it or not, there'll soon come a time when everyone looks back on these as the good old days... Collecting INVINCIBLE IRON MAN #14-19.

description:
Winning isn't everything in the game of basketball, but who wants to come in second? It takes dedication and discipline to be the best, and the Shohoku High hoops team wants to be just that. They have one last year to make their captain's dream of reaching the finals come true--will they do it? Takehiko Inoue's legendary beloved basketball manga is finally here and the tale of a lifetime is in your hands.

Hanamichi Sakuragi's got no game with girls--none at all! It doesn't help that he's known for throwing down at a moment's notice and always coming out on top. A hopeless bruiser, he's been rejected by 50 girls in a row! All that changes when he meets the girl of his dreams, Haruko, and she's actually not afraid of him! When she introduces him to the game of basketball, his life is changed forever...

Starring Hanamichi Sakuragi , a 6" 2' First Year in Shohoku High School who is very unpopular with the lady's. After being rejected over fifty times from fifty different girls, Hanamichi believes he should give up forever. After leaving class he was stopped by a girl named Haruko Akagi, who admires Hanamichi's height. Haruko indroduces Hanamichi to the Shohoku Basketball team. Never stepping on a basketball court in his life, Hanamichi decides to attempt joining the basketball team to impress Haruko and get her attention.

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter #1: Sakuragi
  • Chapter #2: Kaede Rukawa
  • Chapter #3: Blood
  • Chapter #4: The Gorilla
  • Chapter #5: For Love I Will Prevail!
  • Chapter #6: JAM!
  • Chapter #7: I Am Basketballman
  • Chapter #8: Hanamichi Joins the Team
  • Chapter #9: Fundamentals
name: Sakuragi

description: For a self-proclaimed genius such as Sakuragi, executing a dazzling slam dunk is no problem at all, but what about some other basketball moves that require a bit more finesse? With the help of Haruka (and some goading from captain Akagi), Sakuragi attempts to put his pride in check and learn how to pull off a basic layup. In theory it should be easy...but sometimes the simplest shots are the toughest to master.

description:
Crime Goes To College

  Professor Markov opens a Crime School for thugs, and the Black Hood gets a quick education and is sent to the corner. 

 The Case of the Medical Murder

     A hospital becomes the hideout for crime boss Killer Kane, and Dr. Walter Anthony thinks their should be a "pay-off" for helping in his escape.

 The Crime Confessors

  After several days of a violent flood, Bob Dickering and his girlfriend, Thelma Gordon, find refuge in an old church where several others have gathered too. Believing they are about to die, the others begin to confess their sins, but only the Hangman knows who will truly meet their maker.

The Little Crime That Wasn't There

    A nephew wants to inherit his aunt and uncles wealth, and is willing to kill for it.

 Boy Buddies

  Hank Heersatyer, the crooner, is kidnapped, and Dusty and Roy come to his rescue.

Trivia: the oath said by Black hood on the cover is repeated for The Adventures of the Fly #3
name: Crime Goes To College

description:
Headline For Homicide

  An editor starts his own crime newspaper -- The Daily Crime Record -- and the Black Hood is about to make the front page.

The Riddle of Sergeant McGinty's Voice

Sergeant McGinty is accused of making false radio alarms, and the crooks behind it are about to broadcast the demise of the Black Hood.

 New Director of Orphan Asylum

The Black Hood visits a local orphanage to stop a gang of hoods from abusing the kids.

The Crime of the Centuries

   The Hangman vows to catch a killer, even if it takes him 100 years.

 Bill Vigoda Is Unfair To Villains!

  Bill Vigoda, the artist of the strip, helps Dusty find some thugs to scrap with.
